==English==
====Alternative forms====
*(''US'') [[airplane]]

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[aero-]]'', combining form for '''air''' + plane, from Latin ''[[planum]]'', '''flat'''

===Pronunciation===
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /ˈeərəˌpleɪn/ (plural /ˈeərəˌpleɪnz/)

===Noun===
'''aeroplane''' (plural '''aeroplanes''')
# A [[power-driven]], [[heavier-than-air]] [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s that obtains lift by the [[Bernoulli effect]] and is used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]]; a [[plane]].

